# ── Commit Message Format ──
# type(TASK-XXX): short description of what changed and why
#
# Human types: feat, fix, refactor, test, docs, chore
# Agent prefix: agent
#
# Examples:
#   feat(TASK-184): add exponential backoff to Redis queue consumer
#   fix(TASK-201): resolve null pointer in signal scorer on empty payload
#   agent(TASK-184): implement retry logic per spec - workers/queue.go only
#   agent(TASK-184): self-fix: correct delay calculation after CI failure
#
# Rules:
#   - Start with type, then (TASK-XXX), then colon and space
#   - Keep first line under 72 characters
#   - Agent commits must specify which files were modified
#   - Use imperative mood ("add", "fix", not "added", "fixed")
